Regular expressions

A regular expression, or Regex, is a text pattern used to search, validate, extract, split, or replace text. Python provides regular-expression features through the re module.

Common Regex operations include:

Search: Finds the first match anywhere in the text.

Match: Checks for a match at the beginning.

Full match: Checks whether the complete string follows a pattern.

Find all: Returns every match.

Substitute: Replaces matching text.

Split: Divides text using a pattern.

